	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well I want to arrange an interview with a NES game designer who worked around 1990 for a professional company.<br />And ask him such questions :<br />How did they make a game for NES back then?<br />What tools they used for making a nes game?<br />What was the progress?<br />How many people worked on a project?<br />What kind of problems did they have?<br />Any good and bad memory from those days?<br />and some other questions which can be added later<br /><br />But I suggest someone with high reputation (maybe an admin or moderator of nesdev) ask such questions from a professional or at least invite him to come and answer the questions.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
